Decided to make a rocket based off a combination of Nova 5S and Nova 7S. I call it Nova 5-7S. Was about to put a 34 Ton payload into a 1,000 x 1,000 KM orbit. 

Bonus image: Had a little trouble with the custom interstage I made (Was buried inside the collider)
I extract payload from straight Saturn payload adapter but my craft control is locked, and speedometer show 0m/s. Orbital parameters all shows n/a

So... huh... yeah... Got a Titan II (IIIC) core into orbit... I mean, yeah, I have no payload, but still... I'm surprised it made it. Fully fueled Centaur Jr. too.

Thanks to kind contributor Viper, we now have a set of custom Conformal Decals for the Saturn V for realistic recreations. They appear as a new BDB decal part which should come up when you search for "BDB" and "Decal". The colours have been adjusted to fit the KSP re-stockalike palette BDB uses. We might get a few more for Saturn I too.
